Analysis of the Target Structure  
• Block Count & Layers  
  – The finished model uses five total blocks.  
  – There are three “levels” in height:  
     1) The base layer (arch plus two wedges),  
     2) The middle layer (green rectangular block),  
     3) The top layer (the small orange “roof” block).  

• Spatial Arrangement  
  – Centered on the bottom is a red/orange arch (opening faces front).  
  – Flanking the arch on left and right are two matching wedge‐shaped blocks, each leaning outward.  
  – Spanning across the top of all three bottom blocks is a single green rectangular block oriented left‐to‐right.  
  – A single triangular/prism‐shaped orange block sits atop the green block (its apex is visible from the front).  

Selecting Blocks From the Dictionary  
1) Arch Block:  
   – Matches dictionary index 1 (arched opening facing forward, top flat).  
2) Side Wedges (two needed):  
   – Left wedge: index 13  
   – Right wedge: index 14  
   (These two form mirror images leaning outward.)  
3) Green Rectangular Block (middle layer):  
   – Index 5 (green rectangular block, long dimension left–right).  
4) Orange “Roof” Block (on very top):  
   – Index 9 (triangular/prism block).  

Assembly Order  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 1  
  Step2: Move block with index 13  
  Step3: Move block with index 14  
  Step4: Move block with index 5  
  Step5: Move block with index 9  
}
